th care to parent and student incentives—the contributors synthesize an impressive diversity of data, paying special attention to the gross imbalances in educational achievement that still exist between developed and developing countries. They draw out clear implications for governmental policy at a variety of levels, conscious of economic realities such as budget constraints, and point to crucial areas where future research is needed. Offering a wealth of insights into one of the best investments a nation can make, Education Policy in Developing Countries is an essential contribution to this most urgent field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEducation and statezDeveloping countries. 70(DE-588)4003681-90(DE-627)1063888350(DE-576)208852506aAusbildungsförderung2gnd 70(DE-588)4006650-20(DE-627)1063768100(DE-576)208866450aBildung2gnd 70(DE-588)4006660-50(DE-627)1063767800(DE-576)208866507aBildungshilfe2gnd 70(DE-588)4006667-80(DE-627)1063767720(DE-576)208866531aBildungspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4006672-10(DE-627)1063767560(DE-576)208866558aBildungsreform2gnd 70(DE-588)4014948-10(DE-627)1063382340(DE-576)208909966aEntwicklungshilfe2gnd 70(DE-588)4015482-80(DE-627)1063365920(DE-576)208911901aErziehung2gnd 70(DE-588)4066527-60(DE-627)1061132320(DE-576)209164956aWirtschaftswachstum2gnd 70(DE-588)4112628-20(DE-627)10583582X0(DE-576)209469536aAusbildung2gnd 70(DE-588)7859045-00(DE-627)7006331540(DE-576)361772335aEffektivität2gnd 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAlderman, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehrman, Jere R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBleakley, Hoyt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDhaliwal, Iqbal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/